# Write in Ceylon, Deploy in OSGI, or How to push Ceylon inside J2EE applications

The Ceylon language is inherently modular, and is shipped with a complete infrastructure that allows leveraging this modularity out-of-the box.
However Ceylon is not captive of its own infrastructure : After the Java and JS interoperability efforts, the 1.1.0 version has brought out-of-the-box compatibility with OSGI.
